SIMPLE: silent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silent
<hw>Si"lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>silens</ets>,
<ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>silere</ets> to be silent; akin to
Goth. ana-silan.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Free from sound or noise;
absolutely still; perfectly quiet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How <qex>silent</qex> is this town!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not speaking; indisposed to talk; speechless; mute;
taciturn; not loquacious; not talkative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ulysses, adds he, was the most eloquent and most <qex>silent</qex>
of men.</q> <rj><qau>Broome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This new-created world, whereof in hell⟦br⟧
Fame is not <qex>silent</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Keeping at rest; inactive; calm; undisturbed;
<as>as, the wind is <ex>silent</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Parnell. Sir W.
Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Pron.)</fld> <def>Not pronounced; having no sound;
quiescent; <as>as, <it>e</it> is <ex>silent</ex> in
⟦ldquo⟧fable.⟦rdquo⟧</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Having no effect; not operating; inefficient.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cause . . . <qex>silent</qex>, virtueless, and dead.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Silent partner</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Dormant
partner</cref>, under <er>Dormant</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Mute; taciturn; dumb; speechless; quiet; still.
See <er>Mute</er>, and <er>Taciturn</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Silent
<hw>Si"lent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is silent; a time of
silence.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>silent</xex> of the
night.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silentiary</ent>⟦br⟧
